16 provided from the completion of the virtual course.
17 (c) The virtual course is not capable of generating academic
18 credit.
19 (d) The virtual course is inconsistent with the remaining
20 graduation requirements or career interests of the pupil.
21 (e) The pupil has not completed the prerequisite coursework
22 for the requested virtual course or has not demonstrated
23 proficiency in the prerequisite course content.
24 (f) The pupil has failed a previous virtual course in the same
25 subject during the 2 most recent academic years.
26 (g) The virtual course is of insufficient quality or rigor. A
