1 on the basis of race, color, ethnicity, gender, or national origin.
2 Public universities should encourage participation from those who
3 would otherwise not adequately be represented in the student
4 population.
5 (2) The department of labor and economic opportunity shall
6 administer the program described in this section.
7 (3) The amount allocated to each public university is
8 $11,184.00 and is subject to an award period of no more than 2
9 years. Each public university receiving funds for fiscal year 2025-
10 2026 2026-2027 under this section shall report to the department of
11 labor and economic opportunity by April 15, 2026 2027 the amount of
12 its unobligated and unexpended funds as of March 31, 2026 2027 and
13 a plan to expend the remaining funds by the end of the fiscal year.
14 The amount of funding reported as not being expended may be
15 transferred, under the direction of the department, to another
16 public university for use under this section.
17 Sec. 281. (1) Included in the appropriation for fiscal year
18 2025-2026 2026-2027 for each public university in section 236 is
19 funding under the Martin Luther King, Jr. - Cesar Chavez Dolores
20 Huerta – Morris Hood Jr. - Rosa Parks initiative for the Morris
21 Hood, Jr. educator development program, which is intended to
22 increase the number of academically or economically disadvantaged
23 students who enroll in and complete K-12 teacher education programs
24 at the baccalaureate level and teach in this state. Preference may
25 not be given to participants on the basis of race, color,
26 ethnicity, gender, or national origin. Institutions should
27 encourage participation from those who would otherwise not
