8 Sec. 282. (1) Each institution receiving funds for fiscal year
9 2025-2026 2026-2027 under section 278, 279, or 281 shall provide to
10 the department of labor and economic opportunity by April 15, 2026
11 2027 the unobligated and unexpended funds as of March 31, 2026 2027
12 and a plan to expend the remaining funds by the end of the fiscal
13 year. Notwithstanding the award limitations in sections 278 and
14 279, the amount of funding reported as not being expended will be
15 reallocated to the institutions that intend to expend all funding
16 received under section 278, 279, or 281.
17 (2) Funds received for the purpose of administering programs
18 under sections 278, 279, and 281 must not be used for direct
19 financial aid or indirect financial aid. However, a public
20 university may provide academic incentives to motivate
21 participating students as approved by the department. As used in
22 this subsection:
23 (a) "Direct financial aid" includes, but is not limited to,
24 scholarships, payment of tuition, stipends, and work-studies.
25 (b) "Indirect financial aid" includes, but is not limited to,
26 transportation, textbook allowances, child care support, and
27 assistance with medical premiums or expenses.
